Attempts by commercial motorcyclists to cause violence at Idi-Araba area of Lagos State was yesterday prevented by police operatives. Operatives also impounded 130 motorcycles and arrested five suspects following a face-off with an enforcement team deployed to the area. Trouble started after okada riders allegedly resisted officials of the Lagos State Environment and Special Offences Unit from carrying out their duty in the area. Upon sighting the policemen, the motorcyclists mobilised more of their colleagues and set up bonfires, barricaded the roads.   Bamise: Defence counsel’s ill-health stalls trial     2023: Atiku’s emergence cannot mar APC’s chances     World Bank: oil sector challenges threaten Nigeria’s growth    Their action caused panic and paralysed traffic, forcing the policemen to release teargas to control the crowd. The policemen proceeded to seize commercial motorcycles seen in the axis for contravening the ban. Police spokesman Benjamin Hundeyin said “130 bikes were impounded and five suspects arrested”. He said personnel from the Area Command have been drafted there and that there was “absolutely nothing to worry about”.